%md
## Targeing Customers Who Are Most Likley To Buy Insurance
### A Financial Institution wants to provide an additionl product to their customers but want to focus their marketing and selling activities only on those customers who are most likely to be interested in the insurance offering and want to purchase it.

### Let's use Oracle Autonomous Database with its embedded Oracle Machine Learning algorithms to build and apply predictive models to help the Financial Institution target the right customers.

Created and last updated April 2020 by: Charlie Berger, Dhvani Sheth, Siddesh Ujjni

msg.data:
Targeing Customers Who Are Most Likley To Buy Insurance

A Financial Institution wants to provide an additionl product to their customers but want to focus their marketing and selling activities only on those customers who are most likely to be interested in the insurance offering and want to purchase it.

Let's use Oracle Autonomous Database with its embedded Oracle Machine Learning algorithms to build and apply predictive models to help the Financial Institution target the right customers.

Created and last updated April 2020 by: Charlie Berger, Dhvani Sheth, Siddesh Ujjni

paragraphs.title: Display count of people who have purchased insurance vs. those who have not
paragraphs.text:
%sql

SELECT COUNT(CUST_ID) AS TOTAL, BUY_INSURANCE FROM CUST_INSUR_LTV GROUP BY BUY_INSURANCE ORDER BY COUNT(CUST_ID) DESC;

### DATA PREPARATION

paragraphs.title: Stratified Sampling SQL example code to create 60% sample for TRAIN data but with balanced 'Yes' and 'No" target attribute
paragraphs.text:
%script

CREATE OR REPLACE VIEW BUY_INSURANCE_TRAIN_DATA_V AS
SELECT
v1.*
FROM
(

-- randomly divide members of the population into subgroups based on target classes

SELECT a.*,
row_number() OVER (partition by BUY_INSURANCE ORDER BY ORA_HASH(CUST_ID)) "_BUY_INSURANCE"
FROM CUST_INSUR_LTV a
) v1,
(

-- get the count of subgroups based on target classes

SELECT BUY_INSURANCE,

COUNT(*)
"_BUY_INSURANCE_cnt"

FROM CUST_INSUR_LTV GROUP BY BUY_INSURANCE
) v2
WHERE v1. BUY_INSURANCE = v2. BUY_INSURANCE

-- random sample subgroups based on target classes in respect to the sample size

AND ORA_HASH(v1."_BUY_INSURANCE", v2."_BUY_INSURANCE_cnt"-1, 0) > (v2."_BUY_INSURANCE_cnt" * 60 /
100)

paragraphs.title: Stratified Sampling SQL example code to create 40% "hold out" sample for TEST data with balanced 'Yes' and 'No" target attribute
paragraphs.text:
%script

CREATE OR REPLACE VIEW BUY_INSURANCE_TEST_DATA_V as 
SELECT
v1.*
FROM
(

-- randomly divide members of the population into subgroups based on target classes

SELECT a.*,
row_number() OVER (partition by BUY_INSURANCE ORDER BY ORA_HASH(CUST_ID)) "_BUY_INSURANCE"
FROM CUST_INSUR_LTV a
) v1,
(

-- get the count of subgroups based on target classes

SELECT BUY_INSURANCE,
COUNT(*)
"_BUY_INSURANCE_cnt"
FROM CUST_INSUR_LTV GROUP BY BUY_INSURANCE
) v2

WHERE v1. BUY_INSURANCE = v2. BUY_INSURANCE

-- random sample subgroups based on target classes in respect to the sample size

AND ORA_HASH(v1."_BUY_INSURANCE", v2."_BUY_INSURANCE_cnt"-1, 0) > (v2."_BUY_INSURANCE_cnt" * 60 /
100)

paragraphs.title: Create table CUST_INSUR_PREDICTIONS of customers who are predicted to want to buy insurance and are over the AGE of 21
paragraphs.text:
%sql

CREATE TABLE CUST_INSUR_PREDICTIONS AS 
  SELECT CUST_ID, MARITAL_STATUS, FIRST, LAST, STATE, PROFESSION, AGE, PROBABILITY
  FROM (SELECT CUST_ID, MARITAL_STATUS, FIRST, LAST, STATE, PROFESSION, AGE,
               PREDICTION_PROBABILITY(BUY_INSURANCE_CLASS_MODEL_RF, 'Yes' USING *) PROBABILITY
          FROM CUST_INSUR_LTV_APPLY
          WHERE AGE > 21)
ORDER BY PROBABILITY DESC;
